Privacy Policy

Last updated: [05/27/2025]

1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how ADC Entertainment (“we”, “our”, or “us”) collects, uses, and protects personal information when communicating with individuals and businesses via email.
We are committed to respecting your privacy and complying with applicable data protection laws and email communication standards.

2. Information We Collect
We may collect and process the following limited information:
- Email addresses
- Names (If publicly available or provided voluntarily)
- Basic business contact information (If available or publicly available)
- We do not collect sensitive personal data.

3. How We Use Information
Collected information is used strictly for the following purposes:
- Sending service-related or informational communications
- Responding to inquiries or requests
- Providing updates relevant to our services
- We do not sell, rent, trade, or share personal data with third parties for marketing purposes.

4. Source of Email Addresses
Email addresses used for communication are obtained from:
- Publicly available business websites and contact pages
- Professional directories
- Direct inquiries or prior communications initiated by the recipient
- We do not use purchased, scraped, or harvested email lists.

5. Email Communication & Opt-Out
All emails sent by ADC Entertainment:
All emails contain information related to the service, including valid addresses and allowing recipients to delete requests at any time.
Recipients may opt out of future communications by replying to any email with a request to unsubscribe or remove their address.

6. Data Retention
We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfill communication purposes or comply with legal obligations.
Email addresses are removed upon request.

7. Data Security
We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect personal data against unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse.

8. Third-Party Email Infrastructure
Email delivery is handled through trusted third-party providers (such as Mailgun) solely for message transmission.
These providers process data only under our instructions and in compliance with their data protection obligations.

9. Policy Updates
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.
Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated revision date.

10. Contact Information
If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your personal data, please contact us at:
Email: support@helpsender.net

Service Name: HelpSender
Domain: helpsender.net

11. Consent

By receiving communications from ADC Entertainment, you acknowledge that your contact information is used in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
